The error arises because the `@` operator is invalid in an assignment context. Replacing it with a colon to form a ternary condition fixes the issue.

```php
if (x > 0) ? a = 1 : b = 2;
```

However, assigning variables like this isn't directly supported. To fix it properly using if-else:

```php
if (x > 0)
    a = 1;
else
    b = 2;
```

